nightmares. The workaround I can think of is charming them, but this could be difficult, as charming 1 would probably agro the other. Oh well I suppose its worth a shot ...<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=boomshanka>Boomshanka</A> at: 4/1/02 5:56:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualthor64.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Althor64</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 10:10:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4600.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shield of Bane Warding quest (evil races)</span><hr size=1> Since you have your Validus Custodes faction up, kill vamps for Fangs, turn them into the warrior guildleader in Katta ( barbarian in room next to Saumeen Unja ). Give him 4 at a time. You will get Magus Concillium faction, as well as others. Meanwhile, keep any blood and ashes that you get, and after you are no longer KoS to Magus Concillium, turn in the blood and ashes, 4 at a time on each, to Avir Sterbla. More faction hits. I do not think any of these raise Concillium Universus, but it might allow you to do the quest. Then again, it may allow you to do OTHER quests for Concillium Universus faction.. <br><br>Hope it helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umalefic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malefic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 10:32:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb